MSendTo - A command-line mail generation utility for Mercury/32
Mercury Mail Transport System, Copyright (c) 1993-2008, David Harris.
-FT <filename>          Attach a simple text file (no encoding)
-FM <filename>          Attach a valid RFC2822-format mail message
-DELIVERY               Request confirmation of delivery for the message
-TRANSCRIPT <address>   Turn on MercuryE transcript generation to <address>
-INPUT <filename>       Read options from a file (see below)
-SIGNATURE <filename>   Append the specified file to the message body
-QUEUE <directory>      Specify the Mercury submission queue directory
Option specifiers are case-insensitive and can be abbreviated to their first
two characters (e.g: -FR). When using the -INPUT option, you should specify
a text file containing any valid commandline options, one option per line.
MSendTo - A command-line mail generation utility for Mercury/32
Mercury Mail Transport System, Copyright (c) 1993-2008, David Harris.
Configuration mode: MSendTo is going to ask you various questions, and
will use the answers you provide to create a default configuration for
future use. For each settable option, the current setting will be shown
- you can either type in a new value to change it, press <Enter> to leave
it unchanged, or type in a single dash character to unset the item.
Configuration is stored in a file called MSendTo.cfg in the same directory
Queue Directory: enter the location for the Mercury submission queue:
note that this is overridden if -QUEUE is specified on the commandline,
and if no queue is specified anywhere, MSendTo will check the Windows
registry for a queue directory (there will only be a registry entry when
MSendTo is invoked on the machine where Mercury is running).
The current value for this is: %s
Hostname: enter the domain name to use when forming mail addresses.
The current value for this is: %s
Default sender: enter an address to be used as a default 'From' field:
this value is used if no -FROM is specified on the commandline.
The current value for this is: %s
Default recipient: enter an address to be used as a default 'To' field:
this value is used if no To, CC or BCC is specified on the commandline.
The current value for this is: %s
Transcripts: if you want MercuryE transcript generation to be turned on
by default, enter here the address to which transcripts should be sent:
note that -TRANSCRIPT specified on the commandline overrides this value.
If you want MSendTo to generate transcripts automatically using the -FROM
setting on the commandline as the target, type AUTO here.
The current value for this is: %s
